Author:
Vol / Page: 63
Edition:
Quote: The municipal representatives it is true are to be elected by a wide constituency, but the members of the Provincial Legislative Councils are to be elected by the municipal representatives, and not by the people; and the members of the General Assembly to be elected by the members of the Provincial Legislative Councils, to the exclusion of direct popular interference also.
